==English==

===Pronunciation===
*frăg, /fræɡ/, /<tt>fr{g</tt>/
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-æɡ|-æɡ]]

===Etymology===
Shortened from '''[[fragmentation grenade]]'''

===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}}

# {{italbrac|gameplaying}} A successful kill in a deathmatch game.
#:''I'd been fighting him for ages, and then you stole my '''frag'''!''

===Verb===
{{en-verb|frag|g|ing}}

# {{italbrac|US military slang}} To deliberately kill (a member of one's own unit) with a fragmentation grenade.
# {{italbrac|gameplaying}} To kill (another player) in a [[deathmatch]] computer game.
#:''I '''fragged''' him but he fell off the ledge afterwards.''

